# Known divergence: error/notice cursor offset only ("at character N"). NOT a
# multigres bug. multigateway rewrites the submitted query text before
# forwarding it to PostgreSQL (parse + deparse), which shifts the byte offset
# PostgreSQL records for an error/notice cursor. The message text, ordering, and
# every result row are byte-identical to stock PostgreSQL; only the trailing
# "at character N" position differs. This patch records that offset shift so the
# test is verified against multigres's deparsed-query cursor positions.
--- a
+++ b
@@ -6,7 +6,7 @@
 geomfromgeojson_06|MULTIPOLYGON(((0 0,1 1,1 0,0 0)))
 geomfromgeojson_07|MULTIPOLYGON(((0 0,1 1,1 0,0 0)))
 geomfromgeojson_08|MULTIPOLYGON(((0 0,1 1,1 0,0 0)))
-ERROR: Only lon/lat coordinate systems are supported in geography. at character 71
+ERROR: Only lon/lat coordinate systems are supported in geography. at character 77
 #1434: Next two errors
 ERROR: Unable to find 'coordinates' in GeoJSON string
 ERROR: unexpected character (at offset 0)
